'''Dr. Marvin Monroe''' is a [[psychotherapy|psychotherapist]] who first appeared in the first season episode "[[There's No Disgrace Like Home]]". [[Homer Simpson|Homer]] pawns the family television in order to afford a session with Monroe for him and his [[dysfunctional family]]. The failed attempt at therapy culminates with the Simpsons [[electroconvulsive therapy|electroshocking]] each other endlessly, to the point of causing a blackout. Unable to help the Simpsons, Monroe refunds double what the Simpsons paid, and the Simpsons buy a new TV.
